efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n) for initialization, O(1) for changeRating and highestRated
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW 
explanation: The solution utilizes a dictionary `food_ratings` to store food names and their ratings, and another dictionary `cuisine_foods` to map cuisines to lists of (food name, rating) tuples. This allows for efficient lookup and sorting of foods by rating and cuisine. The `changeRating` operation has O(1) time complexity due to direct dictionary access. The `highestRated` operation sorts the cuisine's food list based on rating (descending) and name (lexicographically) in O(n log n) time during initialization.

